cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a novel registration framework using deep neural networks to align multiple point clouds. This involves modeling the scene structure and estimating the occupancy status of global coordinates, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of DNNs as auxiliary functions also implies a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the problem of Lidar SLAM, which suggests a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) for processing Lidar data.
